}stats</a> thay uses dynamic datasets (db queries) but only three predifined ones on some WordPress statistics.<br />\nBoth these plugins use <a href=\"http://sparkline.org/\" target=\"spg\">Sparkline PHP Graphing Library</a>. I was already familiar with this library (which is very good) but there were some minor thing that I wanted different. One thing is multiple datasets in one graph. The thing is that in the code there are traces of possible multiple datasets. On <a href=\"http://sparkline.org/\" target=\"spg\">sparkline.org</a> the last news update is from june 2005. So the development probably stagnated at version 0.2. I tried contacting the creator to see if I could have a go at updating the library but I didn&#8217;t get any response. Altering someone elses code is a bitch anyway so one day of coding later I have my own sparkline library. There&#8217;s still lots of todo&#8217;s but it works.</p>\n<p><!--h3>changelog\n\n\n<table width=\"300\">\n\n\n<tr>\n\n<th>version</th>\n\n\n\n<th>date</th>\n\n\n\n<th>changes</th>\n\n</tr>\n\n\n\n\n<tr>\n\n<td>1.0.1</td>\n\n\n\n<td>2007 01 31</td>\n\n\n\n<td>\n\n<ul>\n\n<li>added header parameter</li>\n\n</ul>\n\n</td>\n\n</tr>\n\n\n</table>\n\n\n\n\n\n<h3>todos</h3>\n\n\n\n\n<ul>\n\n\n<li>sparkline library:\n\n<ul>\n    \n\n<li>start value text</li>\n\n\n    \n\n<li>implement Wu line anti-aliasing where gd doesn't support anti-aliasing</li>\n\n\n    \n\n<li>better variable parsing control</li>\n\n\n    \n\n<li>add 'multi bar' graphic type</li>\n\n\n    \n\n<li>add 'filled line' graphic type</li>\n\n\n    \n\n<li>add 'pie' graphic type</li>\n\n\n    \n\n<li>add 'horizontal bar' graphic type</li>\n\n\n    \n\n<li>add 'bullet' graphic type</li>\n\n\n    \n\n<li>convert data in textual display (abs, exponent etc...)</li>\n\n\n    \n\n<li>insert a smaller font than the default (1) from gd</li>\n\n\n    \n\n<li>recheck modelviewcontroller</li>\n\n\n    \n\n<li>error checking /  debugging</li>\n\n\n    \n\n<li>echo image (as opposed to saving one)</li>\n\n\n</ul>\n\n</li>\n\n\n\n\n<li>plugin:\n\n<ul>\n    \n\n<li>implement static sparklines</li>\n\n\n    \n\n<li>find a better way to parse dynamic datasets</li>\n\n\n    \n\n<li>documentation/examples</li>\n\n\n</ul>\n\n</li>\n\n\n\n\n<li><strike>update original sparkline library to can handle multiple datasets</strike></li>\n\n\n\n\n<li><strike>update original sparkline library to handle transparency.</strike></li>\n\n\n</ul>\n\n\n</p>\n",
